This not only confirms that some dinosaurs had feathers, a theory already widely disseminated, but provides more details than the fossils, such as color and three-dimensional arrangement.
According to scientists, the plumage of this animal was brownish-chestnut in the upper part, with a pale or carotenoid coloration in the lower part.
The discovery also allows us to obtain detailed information about the evolution of the feathers of birds.
Because the plumage of the dinosaur is not equipped with the basic structure, the so-called rachis, but has other characteristics typical of feathers, barbs and barbules, the researchers have concluded that the rachis is probably the result of a subsequent evolutionary development of these characteristics.
The structure of the plumage makes you think that it was not used for flight, but rather for temperature regulation or courtship. Researchers hypothesize that, although it is the tail of a young dinosaur, the specimen shows an adult plumage and not the down of a chick.
According to the hypotheses of the researchers, although the tail belongs to a young dinosaur, the sample reveals a plumage of an adult specimen and not that of a chick.
A car bomb exploded yesterday morning in the headquarters of the police in Gaziantep, Turkey, killing two agents and injuring more than twenty people.
