They have discovered that the functioning of the Sun is based on the same principles as the other stars: the activity of all the stars in the solar system is determined by nothing other than their luminosity and rotation.
The luminosity is used together with the rotation to define the number of Rossby of a star, which is related to the flow of plasma.
The more the Rossby number is low, the lesser is the activity of the star compared to the magnetic inversions.
